  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">City Year recruits and trains young AmeriCorps members to serve as tutors, mentors and role models full-time for an entire year in America&apos;s most underresourced public schools.   This project will enable these corps members to serve over 800 students with targeted interventions for an entire week. The majority of these students are facing the challenges of intergenerational poverty and the schools they attend struggle to meet their needs. City Year aims to help these students reach graduation!</narrative>
  </description>
